title: Hotel YNO
address: No.791/792, Zaya Thukha Street, Myittarnyunt Quarter Township
descriptions: Simple rooms in a down-to-earth budget hotel offering complimentary breakfast & Wi-Fi.
user_reviews: [{"Name":"Arvie A","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QfjHmZg8gr7jpDgKhrh5KsR_Mq7L6pkVedvpKQz-f3LMiOd3OjI90CK4uLtF3wE59zZgA=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Excellent food, friendly staff, and great service. The staff of the hotel is welcoming and always greeting us with a big smile. The manager was fast and communicative. The room condition is nice, bed sheets and linens are clean but I think the bathroom needs cleaning. They always help us to get the things that we need. We were allowed to check in early also (that’s a plus for me). The hotel is a walking a distance to the Yangon Circular Train Station. The hotel manager even took us to Chinatown and Night Market. We appreciate their kind and caring assistance.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Lorendaryl","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QdVsxDWqDDLG62Q3M3dmLlHORJs5jz0NWRJO3cP21KtRNPfosO7RpofjnbUgpyNjOTDew=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Their service is the best. All the staff are very friendly and helpful. They make sure we have everything we need. Their breakfast is very statisfying too-- usually includes rice or noodles, eggs, and fruits.||Also, the distance is okay. It takes us less than 5,000 kyats to get to the downtown/city proper.||||However, I feel like the bathroom needs cleaning especially for molds. The shower's water pressure wasn't good enough too. We had to shower through the faucet. All these could be improved. Other than those, everything was good. Definitely coming back.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Dicey E","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qczn4VDfUM6-AtEt-6oaNazFa-i9Fy6kqPVfGIlPil6vJulEYyK8t930jZwOW4hD80mzw=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Found a hotel in Yangon that suits my quirky sensibility to a “T” – the Hotel Yno in the Tamwee section of the city. ||I’ve tried a few lodging venues around Yangon this last year. For 5 years I used to frequent Fame Hotel on Po Sein Road near scenic Kandawgyi Lake, though this last year management remodeled the rooms making them about half the size they were and raised the room rates.  ||A couple of times I stayed at Uptown Hotel due to its proximity to the Bowling Alley across the thoroughfare; but after the crippling bowling workout my ancient body suffered two months ago I stopped bowling; no more for me. ||Six years ago a rented a pleasant house in the Tamwee area of Yangon and thoroughly enjoyed the neighborhood so I checked on line for hotels situated in those environs. Saw the ad for Hotel Yno and decided to give it a shot. ||First off it’s more economical than Fame or Uptown by a few bucks – half the price of Uptown for more or less the same quality room and so-called complimentary breakfast. But for me it location is superb; within a short walking distance to a cinema, two supermarkets, a bustling outdoor, farmers’ market and at least two halfway decent disco-nightspots for entertainment and possibly companionship. ||The rooms aren’t palatial though not cramped either and have all the amenities travelers look for: speedy wifi, cable TV and hot water shower. The staff is particularly affable and helpful. ||I travel from where I work in Taunggyi to Yangon every two months, I glad I stumbled upon Hotel Yno it is now the place for me.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Paul L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qd0Gzx7-o-W0qn7F-oHhorx-ann6UFYRniBmE7Ar1MhRFtO-x6vY7U2LNCPC1lcQidkpw=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"The location and neighborhood is not great. It's far from Downtown, the main attractions and interesting sights. There is a new mall at 10 minutes by walk where you can find a food court and new supermarket.||||The hotel itself seems very old fashioned but quite clean and the staff is helpful. We used their laundry service and it costed us 3,800 kyats for at leat 11 underpants, 5 tshirts, socks, etc. It took less than a day and our clothes smell good.||||Another annoying point is the presence of mosquitoes. There are a lot, in the corridor, in the bed room.||||If you're planning to visit with a driver and a guide, I suppose it's ok. If you want to walk and visit by yourself, choose a better spot.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Andrew J","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QfjHmZg8gr7jpDgKhrh5KsR_Mq7L6pkVedvpKQz-f3LMiOd3OjI90CK4uLtF3wE59zZgA=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"An average hotel that is nothing to get overly excited about. In the middle of a neighbourhood which is rather quiet and friendly. Close to the train station to use the Yangon circle service which is nice. ||The room wasnt too bad, nothing special but it was simple. Bed was comfortable and the pillow wasnt too bad and comfortable. Plenty of mosquitoes so you need to close the bathroom when in the room as the come through there.||Staff were not overly helpful and the grasp of basic english was quite poor. While very forgivable out on the streets of Yangon, but in the service industry this is a liitle on the poor side. Especially with simple requests unable to be met due to not understanding.||Bathroom facilities were fine and the shower was nice, bear in mind to bring your own toilet paper if you are not a fan of the toilet hose.||Internet was fine on the first night but was severely slow and continuously cutting out and failing to connect.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"L-F or Leong N","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QdVsxDWqDDLG62Q3M3dmLlHORJs5jz0NWRJO3cP21KtRNPfosO7RpofjnbUgpyNjOTDew=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"This was within walking distance of the old railway station which had trains to the city and around Yangon. It was going back 20 years but functional and nostalgic. The hotel was within walking distance of restaurants and eateries and the two opposite were reasonable. The breakfast was buffet and plentiful.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Alex B","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QfjHmZg8gr7jpDgKhrh5KsR_Mq7L6pkVedvpKQz-f3LMiOd3OjI90CK4uLtF3wE59zZgA=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Absolutely basic room: some aunts at the bathroom; shower splashes right into the toilet; no toilet paper provided; heat and mosquitos at night were driving mad.|Breakfast was okay: coffee pots, tea in a tea bags, creamers; sometimes they provide some fruits, sometines not; eggs, rice, noodles, toasts, butter, jam and something else.|Friendly guys at reception.|Don't forget to leave your room keys at the reception if you want the staff to make up your room.|Nice and cheap street food spot right opposite the hotel (noodle soup for 2000 kyats, sateys for 1000 kyats).","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Tammy T","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeCck1CfANpZm9bBk3PHtP97Kh9k25HZfvq9yAWlN3BaIyjSHUPEfWkhAJmuYiJsH-_6g=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"This hotel is basic but ok for a night or two. Does not have 24 hour room service but did point us to a local restaurant. The area is not very touristy, the local restaurant did not have English menu but everyone was helpful and friendly there is also a bakery and convenient store a short walk away.","Images":null,"When":""}]

title: Queen's Park Hotel
address: 132 Anawrahta Rd, Yangon
descriptions: Informal rooms & modern suites in a simple hotel with a Tex-Mex restaurant & a Japanese eatery.
user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Steven Pahuja","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ-XHQCsY-6Xl0R0XgzU1Hgcx7VIYLSmEaV8Ts-YIMxDxUI3g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Despite its very good location in town, the hotel need to be updated a lot to attract visitors.
First -Location ; this the the only upside of this hotel.
Rooms- rooms need to renovate. The smart keys are not working, beds sheets are of ages old, toilet seats screaming to be changed, windows are squeaking, staircase needs to be clean.
Infact everything seems not maintained since twenties.
Service. Nope. So bad. Asked them for a wake up call. Receptionist fall asleep. I mean he has one job. Literally one .
How would I describe this ‘Hotel’?
Not even worth calling it “Guesthouse”","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Saw Moe","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVFG8nGynhketLlqM4u0mV1p0YJ1Zrvgr3MHntQ_6J7rO6fPjKG=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The place is a grace with splendor and majestic in the morning but in the evening after the sun is gone, the place turns creepy. But wait, the rooms are so good and its a true value for money. Rooms are clean and good overall.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kinsay C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QdCjMUwIiBikRhCLHgN_0vyGAo1GvT8DEukiKQb1ujC_eFsFjYrQ0OvLoSxPtqmCdgvFA=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"We have traveled all through southeast Asia and multiple cities in Myanmar. There were rats in the ceiling that could be heard at night. The  sheets were dusty and the hallways / stairs really dirty. Plates of food/ trash were there for days. Free wi fi but poor connection","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Trixsy B","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeCck1CfANpZm9bBk3PHtP97Kh9k25HZfvq9yAWlN3BaIyjSHUPEfWkhAJmuYiJsH-_6g=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Pretty nice place for the price. Did charge US$60 for a rollaway bed for my daughter for 4 nights which was not mentioned earlier. Complimentary breakfast is adequate. I agree that wifi is patchy, but more good than bad.||Would stay here again!!!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Colin R","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeYuXGoFc9HnT35lAJ46cKDIsHY7nNIKUKz_f8yINNlqyrU48jCx-4ctPzihRKgde030w=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Booked a standard single but upgraded to a deluxe double as the standard single can best be described as a fox hole containing a single bed pressed against the wall, a small fridge, a small table, no place to hang your clothes and a bathroom/toilet. The upgraded room cost me US$225 for 5 nights with breakfast. It had 2 beds, 2 chairs, coffee table, kettle, 2 cups and complimentary bottle water(2) and tea/coffee, small fridge, large wardrobe, hairdryer, room phone, in room safe and clean towels every day.||The staff were courteous and helpful. ||This is not a modern hotel but a pleasant hotel to stay in.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"umer k","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QcnOWm00_8Vg0_qD09-e04s-i2bb5F6bVsdwxSboR_yrT1yPvciwzMvgtJ8p5a3bvmZzg=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"My choice for the last one and a half year. The rates are very pocket friendly with newly renovated spacious rooms. The service is fast and friendly. I have tried various floors  and also the presidential suit. The hotel is a minute walk to 24 hr stores including lucky seven tea shop and a big branch of ocean super markets.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"OJ S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QfCm-MBS7Itwd4h-55xcyygsVKq1IZbUTNyg17UKkQsT2C3oSXBlQ_-pGTl8imnrFVtVw=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Decent place to stay at near Yangon's downtown district. Once the lift is back in service I will come back. Although walking up 10 flights of stairs at least twice a day is a pretty good exercise. I've stayed at the Queen's Park before a few years ago. This time I even extended my stay, Clean room, very friendly and helpful staff, breakfast included and it's worth the price. You will get good value for little money. The bed I slept in was incredibly comfy. If the price doesn't accelerate I would always choose this place for my next stay. I cannot give a 5 points rating for the sleep because the hotel is located next to a street junction and gets some traffic noise in the mornings....But I can live with that","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Oo T","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QfCm-MBS7Itwd4h-55xcyygsVKq1IZbUTNyg17UKkQsT2C3oSXBlQ_-pGTl8imnrFVtVw=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Best services and facilities. too expensive.VERY Bad NO good Wi-Fi!

Back then the staff were friendly and the hotel was clean. I stayed here again for 5 days but things were very different! |The aircon and toilet probably hadn’t been cleaned since I was there in 2016. There was no toilet paper in my room so I went to the shop and bought some and they later took it (Probably for someone else who was complaining about not having any toilet paper.) |Staff were not friendly, which is very rare in Myanmar. I asked for a bottle of water and they just looked at me. So I had to go buy water too. |","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Lewis S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QdVsxDWqDDLG62Q3M3dmLlHORJs5jz0NWRJO3cP21KtRNPfosO7RpofjnbUgpyNjOTDew=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"For a hotel that is moderately priced for Yangon standards, one would expect the service and the room to be at the lower end of the spectrum but my partner and I were pleasantly surprised and enjoyed our stay at AKT. The hotel is a little off the beaten track in relation to the CBD of Yangon but is only a 25 minute walk to Bogyoke Aung San market, which is a good opportunity to find your bearings and do a bit of exploring anyhow. ||The room was basic but very comfortable and spacious, including air conditioning and satellite television. The staff were very friendly and attentive, despite occasionally struggling with their English which made some interactions slightly challenging. Free wifi is often touted as a feature in most hotels and guest houses, with varying consistency in connectivity and speed, but the free wifi here was fine for basic things like email and social media. AKT offers a free buffet style breakfast every morning which is a combination of traditional Burmese items such as noodles and also western choices like toast and eggs. ||The only real criticism of the place was that the bathroom and shower were in need of some attention, especially the water pressure in the shower. Otherwise, we would recommend this place to any individual or couple looking to spend a few nights in Yangon on a limited budget","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"victoria m","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QcLvGDdMkm_athQbRQtTYCQxjNUnlrxzopfUA8yGN0YYBZmB4uuNayh0HxTR0N7aNnuMg=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"I book 2 rooms for 1 night to stop over when my return trip from Pyin Oo Lwin to Mandalay. I told them will be there 4:30-5pm. But they just keep on calling me that I will come or not. I replied will be late to check in but definitely will be there. On my way back from Pyin Oo Lwin I called them again because heavy traffic due to lamp pole broke and fall down on street. When I almost reach Mandalay call again and inform I'll be there soon. They said ok. When we check in around 6pm staff just say your room guest not check out so we move you to another sister property hotel. Surprise and upset but no choice as we need to get rest and need to go back yangon early in the morning. When we arrive another hotel we request to see the room they arrange first. 2 room request one room with kind size bed and 1 bed but they arrange 3 beds which we still can accept. Another room king size bed request they said they only have twin bed. I ask staff you want me and my husband to stay in twin bed he said that's all I have. So what is the meaning \"booking/reserve room advance\". As both of us are hotelier we understand book out situation and ROH. But what we expect is simply to say \"sorry\" from hotel.  May be I expect too much on AKT and remind myself not to visit there any more.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Susanne L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeFH6dzZjd_ZFLhXHZKibEzXEy8hWzFB4Qa7PutLe3CnO2G7yVfjd4VSabiCQwQYo5W-g=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"I had to change my first hotel due to conditipns I just could not cope with, so I ended up here. I had a huge room and I smiled for two days straight I was that happy for the plesant surprise. I had room 101 which I recomend single or cuples to ask for, or maybe 201 or 301. I had an extra night in yangon on my way to bangkok and booked here again, but got a different room. Same, lovely bed but the room was smaller so thats why i recomend the other room. I was here on a research trip so i spent some time in my room. But if thats not something you are going to do, any room here will serve you very well. Electricity and airncon all day long, wifi in room and very friendly staff. I wilø deff stay here again when i come back.","Images":null,"When":""}]

title: Hotel City
address: R59H+PH9 Hotel City, Tayoke Paya Kyaung St, Yangon
user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Meikhtilar Steel Structure","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV40oqjASaBkvTUjHhtYIX53dyr84vL5Wtn9ZvYr9j7aNk2HQs=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Unpleasant Experience, Misleading Policies

I recently stayed at this hotel and had a highly disappointing experience. When I booked a double bed room, I assumed it would accommodate my family, including my two children. To my dismay, upon arrival, I was informed that the hotel's policy only allowed one child in a double room without extra charges.

Not only was this policy not clearly stated during the booking process, but I also had to pay additional fees for my second child, making the stay much more expensive than anticipated. This felt like a blatant attempt to squeeze more money out of guests, and I found it completely unacceptable.

Furthermore, when I tried to discuss this issue with the staff, they were unhelpful and dismissive, showing a lack of empathy towards my situation. The lack of transparency and the way I was treated left a bitter taste in my mouth.

I would strongly advise potential guests to thoroughly review the hotel's policies before booking, as this experience has left me feeling deceived and dissatisfied. I will not be returning to this hotel in the future.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Sai Htun Htun Oo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWUtIcSSlih268kO5CMKZquOQ7NxsUSK16LRUUBWjDPu1yRWGat=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"2 Stars hotel. Thats where the negatives stop. ||||Firstly lets put this in perspctive,our room cost 63 usd (20 bucks each) including a very nice breakfast. ||||On arrival we were greeted with an orange juice and taken to our room by 3 porters lugging our bags up 4 stories to our room. But both room doesn't have a football line.

We had a nice room on 5th floor with view over the river. The hotel and bathrooms are nice and clean. The pineappel pancake was our favourite room service order, which you can order from 24/7 :-)","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Nwè T","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeNj0UTN0yIrCGyJ0JhWwDODOg5QjAH0gdfB9Ji-oFl0zWFI-YVmhNAr-FGLycdpIjFmw=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"I stayed there for 5 nights in a double room for single occupancy. It was a convenient, comfortable and pleasant stay. ||The room was spacious, very clean, well furnished and provided with an electric kettle, a hospitality tray (bags of green tea), bottled water and a chargeable minibar (mini fridge). It was not a standard double room; so it had a walk-in shower/ wet room instead of a bath. The extractor fan worked very slowly but it did not disrupt my daily plans. Electricity was reliable to use the air conditioning throughout the night. Internet was slow but usable to keep in touch with the world. ||Restaurant on the ground floor was small but served nice and inexpensive Chinese and Burmese dishes. I had no tummy ache! A limited variety of local breakfast was served at 7 am and continental  breakfast (cornflakes and milk, fresh fruits, juice, filtered coffee) was also available. You could order food 24 hours a day as well!||There is a spa (I had no time to try it) and a laundry service (it did the basic job). An ATM is just at the front of the hotel. The hotel's vehicle is a 7-seater, with air conditioning, which you can hire at a very reasonable price especially if you're travelling in a group of more than 3 (the max number to fit in comfortably a taxi). It takes at least an hour, due to worsening traffic jams, to get to the city centre and usual tourist attractions. ||Staff were very polite, attentive and always willing to help. Many showed a good knowledge of the local area. The owner and manager were extremely pleasant and helpful and keen to improve the quality of service that their hotel provides. ||It is a new hotel in the outskirts of Yangon which used to be a poor suburb built about 50 years ago. It is only about 10 minutes taxi ride from a big and busy shopping mall called "Capital", a restaurant chain called "Shwe Pazun" and a park where demo ethnic villages are built for local visitors as well as tourists (there is a fee which I don't know). The traffic on the road in front was busy in the day but it died down as the night went by. ||All in all, it offers a very good value for money if you are a customer with realistic expectations and wants an all-in-one inexpensive stop in Yangon. I'd stay there again when I'm in Yangon next time.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Audrey Y","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QfjHmZg8gr7jpDgKhrh5KsR_Mq7L6pkVedvpKQz-f3LMiOd3OjI90CK4uLtF3wE59zZgA=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Wonderful staff - speaking enough English to be really helpful. title: Asian Smile Hotel
address: No. 324, Thanthumar Road, Thuwanna, Yangon 11072
user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Brandon Rudd","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL3BEm67ErtBvBTnTEY_JdnDPNZmcEPQkFQ8FQpZRsN2KeORA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"An amazing place to stay if you really want to get lost in Myanmar! The staff are super kind and helpful, alongside being quite amusing at times.

They may not speak much English but they more than make up for it with service, not to mention they are very generous. A person here let me borrow some flip flops for the time I went to pagoda and helped me dress in their traditional outfit. Thanks to them I have a great experience in the country.

The location is pretty convenient too if you use the grab app, you can book a taxi and take a ride to downtown in about 10 minutes.

The room also has all the basic necessities and even come with free body wash and shampoo incase you run out as well as toothbrush.

The power may go out a few times but thats not their fault, its the countries power grid with rolling blackouts and they try to keep the power going with a generator I believe. The hot water in the shower is a little short but with how hot the country is it didn't bother me.

Hopefully they see this so thank you Asian Smile Hotel!!!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Myo Myint oo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXOmactE_SsuEBl2unndIH-zfOLgexF7ZWcsQAWzZo2mqLLULTKcA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Wide and clean room. This is a mid-range hotel on Yangon’s scale of things. The staff is very nice and attentive to guests, always smiling and on hand to help with requests and enquiries. My room was clean and tidy, it had an AC and a king size bed with clean linen and comfortable pillows. There were a tele and a minibar in the room as well. The bathroom had both a bath and a shower. The room would be cleaned every day, toiletries and linen on the bed replaced. A diverse buffet breakfast was served every morning: there was a big board with Asian breakfast choices as well as a small table with fried eggs, toasts and coffee. It was definitely worth the money I paid. Hotels in Yangon are expensive, sometimes you pay more than you would in London, therefore Holiday was a good find. ||||A couple of cons: ||1 - Sound insulation is poor, you would head other guests returning at night. Lake at the end of Phoe Sein Road is a pleasant outing.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Amini K","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QfjHmZg8gr7jpDgKhrh5KsR_Mq7L6pkVedvpKQz-f3LMiOd3OjI90CK4uLtF3wE59zZgA=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"We stayed for nearly a night at the Holiday Hotel in Yangon, Myanmar in May 2014. On our way from Hanoi to Bagan, we had to spend a night here before catching our plane to Bagan the next day. Upon arriving in Yangon, the hotel does not offer transportation from the airport so we took a taxi for about $10 USD. The hotel is about 20 minutes from the airport. Staff was friendly as the hotel is family owned. Since we left very early the next morning (around 4am) we were not able to experience the breakfast but complimentary water in the room was nice. Rooms are a bit small but clean and with A/C and TV. Elevator functions well. The rooms are otherwise basic. We found the price of hotels in Yangon expensive (over $100) but in our case we didn't have too much of a choice unless we slept at the airport. While the pool size is impressive and having two of them is a great convenience, I did notice that there is room for improvement in terms of cleanliness. I understand that maintaining a public pool can be a challenging task, but I believe that more effort can be put into ensuring it is kept clean and hygienic.

In terms of pricing, I found the swimming fee of 10000 to be reasonable, but I do feel that the current state of cleanliness does not justify the cost. I believe that a lower fee would be more appropriate given the current conditions.

I also had the opportunity to try the food, which was average in quality. However, I did find the prices to be on the higher side. I recommend reviewing the pricing strategy to ensure that it is aligned with the quality of the food.

On a positive note, I was impressed with the cleanliness of the bathroom facilities. They were well-maintained and provided a good experience.

title: Thiri Mingalar Hotel

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Brian d","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QfHhPp0vyvo1Wo3WY4NH1G5QOPAHGBMv_XiebXLZtHzVwVa3wkRhb3dykyKrUCZPlawDA=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"I told the owner eventually I'd give her hotel the top rating it deserves, and here it is.||||There's really only 1 or 2 places in Yangon to see, and they are both pretty close to this hotel. They are of course Shwedagon, & the floating restaurant structure on the lake. The cheap-o guest houses occupied by the budget backpackers- which I am usually one of- are at least 45 minutes away from Shwedagon by taxi.  Taxis are cheap, but why bother sitting in a taxi for at least 90 minutes to get there & back when you can do it a little cheaper and spend 20 minutes r/t in a taxi and come back to a great little pearl of an unknown hotel? Even the bellmen at the $125/night hotels who sincerely tried to help me find an affordable hotel nearby all had absolutely no idea this hotel even existed.||||Anywhere near Shwedagon, you're gonna pay at least $60 for a crappy hotel, and easily well above $100 per night. title: Sky Star Hotel
address: No. 51/B, Sky Star Hotel, 1 E Horse Race Course Rd, Yangon 11211
descriptions: Warm rooms & suites in an informal hotel with a restaurant & a bar, plus an outdoor pool & a spa.
user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Javier Sona","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXQnUd27AKg9svga9_QET4x2Sxq9FHmO9iXd1BsfC-x9wK75Dqx=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Review of My Stay

I travel quite a lot, and I have to say it’s been a long time since I’ve encountered such pleasant people. They make you feel at home, always with a smile and ready to help. The staff is outstanding.

The Location: The cleanliness is exquisite, the rooms are bright, new, and have a modern style with great design. The beds are super comfortable, and when you close the curtains, it’s completely dark, allowing for ideal rest. The rooms are spacious and tidy, with a practical and clean bathroom, and a large wardrobe for storing clothes. The security is excellent, and the atmosphere is pleasant and tranquil, featuring pools on the terrace.

Food: The dining is excellent and very reasonably priced.

I’m genuinely surprised because I’ve tried to find a flaw but haven’t been able to.

Before this hotel, I stayed at a typical resort where the crowds, noise, and activities overwhelm any sense of tranquility. Upon arriving here, I quickly felt at home, relaxed, and thoroughly enjoyed the experience.

It’s a pleasure to be in a hotel that combines the warmth of a cozy establishment with the comfort and decor of a high-end hotel.

I highly recommend it. I can’t express enough gratitude to the staff and the manager, who treats guests with enthusiasm and warmth, paying close attention to every detail.

In short: warmth, comfort, cleanliness, incredible infrastructure, magnificent service, and a tranquil environment—100% recommendable. This is undoubtedly an experience I won’t forget and hope to repeat.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"SOE HTET","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWla-Ejww2zw_KCGErgsdgiUOsBpNjlzrMuMerAJwsP_Y-oSams=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Sky Star Hotel in Yangon exceeded my expectations! The rooms were clean, spacious, and well-equipped with modern amenities. The staff was exceptionally friendly and attentive, always ready to assist with a smile. The breakfast buffet offered a delightful variety of both local and international dishes. The rooftop pool provided stunning views of the city, making it a perfect spot to relax after a day of sightseeing. Conveniently located, it was easy to explore nearby attractions. Highly recommend for a comfortable and enjoyable stay!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Min Thant Tun","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJHj-v24ZNvoB7xZA_ljYGVj2N_Ibyq5b6OLx6d1t14i1o2nQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I just going there to attend a wedding reception. It's wedding hall are very good.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jason Todd","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUtwz3_D32i0UXA6hmR_0O2DBkoqJk-X8HAOWB3s9tyMlfaQ5HC=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Not so bad worth to pay","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Arkar Guison","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocINAuEPBdkpDDPDpUy0jm6p5GoFbGwfJtg7eBxBMPEzg9Cv0d0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Rooms are clean and best place to relax with the friends. But sometimes the place turns into creepy one because the frightening and invisible ghost exist.I heard that this place is located in the destroyed grave but I am not sure if this is a myth or reality.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN0djz0O5kUfxtDb7emBmJwn2tN44CuO86QVIgb&fid=0x0:0x9fae3b92080471be"],"When":"2024-1-4"},{"Name":"sammie J","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeSe9ibNVY65MpgeQh70I370foM0-7tEPyVc9CIfSq5Ekli093sZJVPBoLD5d5qPK_2rw=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"The hotel boasts a giant 9 floor building at the end of a driveway and has a grand entrance with huge sparkling balls hanging from the ceiling, which suggests some sort of elegance. The staff greet you with huge helpful smiles and are indeed friendly and welcoming. The room was clean and comfortable, however there was a musty smell to the room. Perhaps the result of  past smoking in the room?  Decor wise the whole place is dated and makes me feel like I've stepped into a 90's film actually some parts resembled the Titanic! I kinda liked that but whatever floats your boat I guess! I can deal with it for a night. I was super happy with the gym, which was clean and well equipt. The pool area is nice but looks a bit like an oasis in a desert. There is huge space around the pool that is used for functions. My purpose for booking this hotel was for the use of the gym and pool before a late night flight the day after. I wanted to spend my last day chilling by the pool but there was indeed a poolside funtion, which meant the pool was closed. I explained my purpose for booking to the manager and he was understanding and allowed me to swim while the staff were preping the event. I am very pleased with his understanding of this situation. Though still slightly frustrated that I could'nt spend my last day by the pool. Instead I reclined in true 90's style overlooking the roof tops of Yangon on my dusty balcony and took full advantage of the 1pm late check out.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Marissa C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qf66pF81jsVXBxevYxxL5FsdlDsKAngAUpJVE-hAwai1rl8J0QnYqktKV3UGdpbmNlc_A=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"This hotel is pretty great.  The staff is AMAZING!  They are so friendly and helpful.  The breakfast buffet is huge and a great selection of food.  Pools is fun and nice.||The only exception was the room was in need of a little tlc.  Wall paper was just starting to peel and a little bit of mold around the A/C unit.||other than that it's a very nice hotel.||There is not much around if you like to walk around.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ko Pauk","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUUOCsxZ3_Jdk6ms5EJ9O-ozAEJWBZXJn6a0EFTsP4gTQ8WaJORvA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"As for me, it's the worst hotel I've ever experienced. I would like to get a bottle of wine. Of course, I called room service. Five times I called, didn't get response. It was 1 am. I thought room service has closed so I tried to sleep.

Then I received a call from room service, I said I want wine. If they responded not available, I would be totally fine. But what they did is they talk each other (fortunately or unfortunately, I heard over phone), one of them blame the one who answer the call why he didn't said it's not available. The reason is they are lazy to bring a bottle of wine.

The amenities seem good but not really. Conditioner bottle has broken, water tap is broken, towels are really bad smell.

Next morning, breakfast time, ordering omelette made me disappointed from the cook.

I recommend not to go this hotel. Please email me for more info.

I am really disappointed this hotel.","Images":null,"When":""}]

We took a superior room which was spacious and comfortable. Breakfast in the patio downstairs was good and it's possible to order a local breakfast. WIFI worked well. The staff is wonderful and helpful. I highly recommend this hotel, especially as a getaway from the hectic, chaotic center of the city.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Douglas B","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qczn4VDfUM6-AtEt-6oaNazFa-i9Fy6kqPVfGIlPil6vJulEYyK8t930jZwOW4hD80mzw=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"This inn is essentially a private house converted into rooms. The manager/owner speaks good English, the other helpful staff not so much.||||I had a large room with the door right next to the entrance. It was still quiet and with the property off the road and surrounded by trees it is mostly the sounds of birds that might disturb one. The room was clean, bed comfortable, a/c, fridge, safe. Bathroom smallish but fine, big shower. Soap, shampoo provided.||||TV but only 2 channels - movies and lifestyle. But good wifi. No restaurant on site but a good and popular local restaurant within 5min walk. Western restaurants a bit further. Drinks available at the inn. Breakfast consists of 4 choices - 3 local meals or a plain omelette served with toast and fruit. ||||Can walk to park and lake; could walk to pagoda and town if keen on walking but calling a taxi could be easier.||||Needed to stay in Yangon an extra day for rest and had no problem deciding to stay on that extra day at 100 Moon Inn. If you are after being closer to the nightlife action this might not be the place for you.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Saran W","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeFH6dzZjd_ZFLhXHZKibEzXEy8hWzFB4Qa7PutLe3CnO2G7yVfjd4VSabiCQwQYo5W-g=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"We decided to book this hotel based on the review from Trip advisor website. We stayed there for three nights. The room is larger than my expectation. The location is on the alley of the street , privacy, quiet, and its near to downtown. The breakfast is fantastic.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Truc V","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeCck1CfANpZm9bBk3PHtP97Kh9k25HZfvq9yAWlN3BaIyjSHUPEfWkhAJmuYiJsH-_6g=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Positives||- Large triple room, very spacious albeit a bit dark||- One queen bed and a large single bed||- Quite place away from the busy, dusty streets||- The owner will buy and deliver food from the closest Chinese restaurant for you||- One of the boys will run and fetch a taxi for you when requested||- Decent house, tastefully decorated, comfortable room and comfy beds, friendly staff||||||1) Sunday night mosquito fumigation||On our very first night there, between 1800-1900 hours just after putting baby to sleep, as I was sitting on the bed I heard this deafening lawn mower noise coming closer and closer to us, then it stopped.  And all of the sudden it was hard to breath and I could not see much of the sitting area because the whole room was filled with smoke!  I quickly grabbed the sleeping baby, ran out of the room upstairs to the reception area to ask what was wrong!  With very limited English the owner later managed to tell me that it was the regular Sunday night mosquito fumigation and somehow the fumes got into our room.||||He knew about it and yet did nothing to warn us, knowing full well that we checked in with a small baby.||||Not acceptable.||||||2) Room change||Understandably I was very worried about the toxicity of the fumes and our baby, requested that we change room to another one that's the same size and setup.  There was only one tripple room, all other rooms were smaller which meant a downgrade, but the owner refused to give a discount even if we downgrade to a smaller room to avoid the smoke.||We ended up having to wait until the smoke cleared, coming back to and sleeping in the same room that night.||||Such welcoming event on our first night.  It was an extremely stressful experience, had we not pre-paid for the 3 nights we would have moved hotel the very next morning!||||Two big thumbs down for this experience and the owner's customer service alone.  Well, no customer service to speak of.||||||3) Too many mosquitoes, no mosquito net!||So with mosquitoes everywhere outside, and quite a few inside the room all the three of us got bitten everynight.  Our poor one year old baby, she got bitten every night, on her legs, arms and face.||||Definitely don't recommend staying here with kids.  You get eaten alive by mosquitoes in the room.||||||4) Housekeeping \u0026 room cleaning||Even though fresh towels and sheets are changed everyday, however there is a lot left to be desired in the housekeeping department when it comes to room cleaning service.||||The mop was used for the entire room without being washed because a water bucket was nowhere to be seen during the operation.  So afterwards, even though the entire floor was mopped it still felt dirty and our feet got dirty in minutes again.||||Air freshener was used but it actually was stinky and quite suffocating!||||||5) No room service for breakfast||Despite having pre-ordered our breakfasts, the next morning when I rang reception, the owner refused to have breakfast brought to our room.  We ended up feeding our baby in the room, then having breakfast in the courtyard later, which pretty much took the whole morning.  By the time we finished breakfast and managed to get out of the house, it was 11am!||Subsequent mornings, after even more repeat requests they reluctantly brought breakfasts to our room so we could eat and feed our child at the same time to save time.||||It should not be that difficult with room service, it's pretty normal, especially given we have a little baby with us.||||This BnB is not at all baby friendly.||||||6) Very limited English||No one at this BnB could speak English adequately so they can make themselves understood, nor could they understand my requests without me having to repeat them for the nth time.||- the young boys could understand some but not speak English at all||- the owner misunderstood my request for dinner, ordered too many dishes for 2 people||- the owner misunderstood my request for taxi to the airport, instead of waiting for me to call reception around 10am, a taxi was ordered in exact at 10am.  The taxi driver ended up waiting for nearly an hour before we were ready.||||||It's a family business, so obviously they tried their best but their service still need many improvements to make it worth while.||||||Overall, it was barely a satisfactory stay given the problems described above.  The fact the fumes from the mosquito fumigation got into our room while baby was sleeping and the owner did not let us know in advance was unacceptable.  Adequate English is a must to ensure sufficient communication.||||The best tips I can give you||Tip #1: if you are planning to stay on a Sunday night, check with them about mosquito fumigation||Tip #2: use an English/Burmese translator (such as Google Translate) to avoid misunderstandings||Tip #3: the BnB is always almost empty, so you probably don't need to book so many nights in advance.  Stay for a couple of nights first and see if it's worth the budget option.||||Recommendation?  Only if the owner improves on those points mentioned above, then yes.||||For me, I will be staying elsewhere next time around.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Sharon B","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeFH6dzZjd_ZFLhXHZKibEzXEy8hWzFB4Qa7PutLe3CnO2G7yVfjd4VSabiCQwQYo5W-g=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Very comfortable bed, serviceable room with everything we needed, brilliant breakfast, super helpful staff, easy access to downtown Yangon via taxi, close walk to Ocean Supermarket.  Will definitely stay again!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Tony B","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeCck1CfANpZm9bBk3PHtP97Kh9k25HZfvq9yAWlN3BaIyjSHUPEfWkhAJmuYiJsH-_6g=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Reasonable price with a private room / good WIFI /  many selection of breakfast/ hot shower / perfect location, it's near to everywhere/ the best choice for travelling into Yangon. warm hospitality. Totally recommend it","Images":null,"When":""}]

title: Millennium Hotel
address: Q59F+WF7 Millennium Hotel, No 7 54th St, Yangon 11121
descriptions: Airy rooms in a low-key hotel offering a restaurant with a terrace & panoramic river views.
user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Ivan Chin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXoWpmpqXPPdu6CyZ9H6hDLNz_fi9gQe8APeLCtpN-SUnR5okEO=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Old hotel but friendly & nice staff。
Location is not in place of interest but hidden in a small alley.
Surround with residential area and a school just right at street end which you can join in with there local activities.
I have been staying in this hotel for a few times as for Business visiting.
Is so safe that I can come back alone without worrying.
The restaurant is on the top level, which you can enjoy the early sun rise together with your B/F.
The far end with the rivers view with all the busy activities to go along with.
You could saw a beautiful Pagoda temple at the river side with there Port crane side by side.
Would still be staying on my next visit","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Alan C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QfjHmZg8gr7jpDgKhrh5KsR_Mq7L6pkVedvpKQz-f3LMiOd3OjI90CK4uLtF3wE59zZgA=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"I stayed here in Nov 2015 and then booked my wife and daughter into it in Dec 2015. I don't think it's the best value for money but compared to the place I first stayed in on arriving into Yangon (rats) it was great. The rooms were dated for sure(doesn't bother us) but clean ( like this) and the bed comfy (like this). Bathrooms were clean but again a little dated, first room it seemed like bathroom was a retrofit after thought (again doesn't bother me). wifi useless but just pick Iona cheap sim - problem solved.  The location is a little out of main town centre but I liked it, although you do feel it during the day when the sun is glaring. Sidewalks are poor to non existent so if you have a walking child you need to be extra careful. If you have a buggy it's going to be a bit of a pain but doable. Night time is much better temp wise but it does feel a little dark and dingy walking back/to the hotel in sections of road near the hotel. Personally I didn't feel uncomfortable at all but I could see how others may, I'd say cut off the river frontage road and cut back into one of the busier streets and use theses for majority of walking to and fro. Some nice restaurant nearby. I'd stay again for sure but would be looking for a little better deal.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Don S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qczn4VDfUM6-AtEt-6oaNazFa-i9Fy6kqPVfGIlPil6vJulEYyK8t930jZwOW4hD80mzw=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Went back to this hotel after three years and it is showing a few signs of wear.  However, it is clean and I would still regard it as good value - hotel prices in Yangon are exorbitant.. Very good view from the breakfast restaurant on the rooftop. Staff is very friendly and helpful, and I feel secure here. There is also a taxi driver with a powerful car just across the road who will get you to the airport or anywhere else in no time at a very good price. This is by no means a 5-star hotel, but it's good enough for me.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Glenn E","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QdHDxxyBDO6igPA51sqxYAI1TTeuGvapT1sWSCJfPSgzOZltNlMhWmUDpj2A3v7zAw89g=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Staff were very friendly. Hotel is very tired, our room was very small, clean...but small. Bathroom very tired. Location is away from the city along the river front......nothing to really walk to. Breakfast is an all asian affair and very very good. The restaurant is located at the top of the hotel and offers great views around the city. I would rate this as transit hotel, somewhere to put your head down for the night, for a good rate","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"dave J","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QchZeuqqdsc2mxTzAL46o1Zp-eQpx0fXItgIlFx_-eADsDQzpyjY9GuirM6XH9EgCdepg=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Stayed here for three nights. And the staff serving at breakfast were truly charming.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kan C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QdCjMUwIiBikRhCLHgN_0vyGAo1GvT8DEukiKQb1ujC_eFsFjYrQ0OvLoSxPtqmCdgvFA=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"This was a short trip and I stayed just a night at the hotel. Overall it was good and I would stay here agin. ||||The view at the rooftop is great. What truly sets the Grand Galaxy Hotel apart is the outstanding service. The staff members are not only professional but also warm and welcoming. Whether it was a request for room service or assistance with local recommendations, the staff was always ready to help with a smile.

Dining at the hotel was a highlight of my stay. The variety of culinary options catered to every taste, and the quality of the food was outstanding. The chefs clearly prioritize using fresh and high-quality ingredients, creating a memorable dining experience.

The hotel's amenities are top-notch with a well-equipped fitness center.

The Grand Galaxy Hotel's location is also worth mentioning. It's conveniently situated, allowing easy access to key attractions and making it a great base for both business and leisure travelers.
Overall, my experience at the Grand Galaxy Hotel was exceptional. I would highly recommend it to anyone looking for a blend of luxury, comfort, and outstanding service. title: CITY HOTEL YANGON
address: No.170/176 Bo Aung Kyaw St, Yangon MMR013017701
descriptions: Laid-back lodging offering airy rooms with free Wi-Fi, plus a classic restaurant.
user_reviews:
[{"Name":"mike mcconnell","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI8njdbK4li0fOk498GbMSFQykgWC58oFCs-Z3ouX2eELA7Tg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We loved staying here, and for us it was luxury. We are on extended travels and on a budget, so are used to lesser accomodations. The room was large with many nice amenities.
There was a large tub and they even had bubble bath! There was a table to write at, and a table with two chairs to play cards or enjoy the provided coffee. There was also a closet and luggage rack. The breakfasts were buffet style and different every day. There were many selections to choose from.

The hotel is dated and a bit worn, but they are currently undergoing renovations. The staff and manager were very nice, attentive and helpful. We really enjoyed our stay here, and would definitely stay again!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Uli T","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QenZcshuv-mcTaHpijHYR7rD8aAfHNd_sW64kn-Y5YjDT8OPIb2-VibdC_Ge2Xr-2EV5A=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"This local style hotel (good middle class) is located close to the River, the British Embassy and in walking distance to the famous Sule Pagoda, shopping areas, as well as to the train station (for people who want to experience the adventures train ride i.e. to the North) and places to visit can easily reached by bus – i.e. the must to visit in the city -  the world heritage Schwedagon Pagoda.||||The 11 stories high hotel covers many groups (mainly customers from Asia) but that don’t disturbe individual guests.  By requesting an upper floor room, I got an upgrade to a  simple, clean but very big room, facing the river side. ||Drinking water, water heater and coffee bags are provided and bed linen will be changed every day.   A/C cools down the room temperature from sometimes outside 35C. down to a temperature of your convenience.  The hotel itself is a bit run down, but the rooms are clean and of course need some renovation. ||So I would recommend to invest some more of the planned travel budget and ask for a renovated room with western standard and a nice view to the River and Harbor - it would be worth it.  In rooms on lower levels you have a great chance only to look to the wall of next door building!||The variety of the free buffet breakfast (Asian+European style commenced in a Thai restaurant on the ground floor) is good and convenient. Expect coffe/ tea in the typical almost creamy and sweet local style.||The friendly staff does not always speak English, but tries to find a colleague that can. The very active and friendly GM (Mr Than Ko Lin, called Collin) will help you as well to satisfy your needs.  Even late check-out can be arranged.||I stayed there for a few days and was all over satisfied and would stay there again.||Next to the reception you find a counter of a travel agency that provides all kinds of travel bookings for your convenience.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Milica djordjevic","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUbb55xNwrh4-p8XjQ3bwjOCDxKRPUCyG4hoaGXjaMWwnTi1ocvxw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"The place is pretty run down. I asked for early check in and a large bed but they didn't reply at all to my request. Upon arrival I had to wait for check in in the lobby and they gave me a room with two singles after telling me they were going to give me a room with a large bed. Breakfast was fine. The room was pretty noisy with the building next door cms away from the one window which couldn't be opened.The bathroom was in pretty bad shape. It wasn't as dirty as some rooms I've seen in Myanmar but I can't  say it was clean.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"djanaka","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QchZeuqqdsc2mxTzAL46o1Zp-eQpx0fXItgIlFx_-eADsDQzpyjY9GuirM6XH9EgCdepg=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"We arrived quite early on our flight from Malaysia. The buffet  is nice and delicious. I want to say thanks to the night shift staff guy who helped me to print out my documents while all shops were closed during the night. I would highly recommend this hotel for those who come and visit to Yangon. Pictures on the internet are obscenely misleading. The owner / management can use the yellow pages listing kept in the room to find out a vendor from the era of 2020, who would know to fit tiles and does the grooving neatly. Also this change can only be brought about by the owners if they believe and have faith in the fact that a neat washroom is an integral part of hotel accommodation. This place is a total waste of money, there are far better options in and around. I would reiterate, old-age of the property is not the problem, I have enjoyed staying at old properties in the past, they have carried their age graciously, the neglect or lack of belief in a clean hygienic environment is the grey area.","Images":null,"When":""}]

title: Hotel War Dan
address: No. 85/86, Wardan St, Bahosi housing complex, Lanmadaw Twonship, Yangon
descriptions: Simple rooms in an unpretentious hotel featuring a laid-back restaurant, plus free parking & Wi-Fi.
complete_address: {"borough":"","street":"No. 85/86, Wardan St, Bahosi housing complex, Lanmadaw Twonship","city":"Yangon","postal_code":"","state":"","country":"MM"}
user_reviews: [{"Name":"Venkatesh Ganesan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVBU1NdT-cvYu_kVD7ku1bYuAO6ndUeintnUcPbPAkTkRvbRpBRuA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The staffs were very nice and helpful. Even though the hotel looks little older from outside, it was nice in interior. Little costly but spacious, clean and quiet. Breakfast was very good","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"annbramnora","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QdrOaBwvzVCVZGa_JCxmRob18-RTGR2NAc2ehM2ioIFQuUJBtaO6jr7GHqX15LV00VYsw=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"We stayed at Wardan twice. It is a nice hotel for a few nights in the city and it is still quite affordable. Room was ok, not very big. Bed quite hard, but that's the way they generally are in Myanmar. Bathroom was fine with a good shower. During our first stay we had a room on the first floor and ther were quite a few mosquitos in the bathroom. During our second stay we had a room on the fifth floor and we didn't have that problem there. Everything is really clean. Hotel is very new. It is almost impossible to communicate with the staff, they barely speak English. However, they are really friendly. Breakfast is quite poor, only a few options and all Birmese style, only white toast available if you wish to have a Western style breakfast. ||We paid with creditcard once, this is possible, although they add 4% to your bill.||All in all, considering the high costs of hotels in Yangon, I would go back here again.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Raymond K","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QfnSFWXMd1oJu73a6IhdtgibYcjse2HKQTHeghNQd9Cyw8DYQQJZDCyh-TD68ehXuY-FA=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"I have read some of the reviews but some things must have changed or I am just here in the off peak season.  The room is quite spacious with 2 beds. The shower is very spacious and looks newly installed with no leaks and the drain works very well. The room service is perfect with the tea and coffee sachets replaced daily. I find the area is quiet as well. |I was disappointed initially to be away from the beer and favourite restaurants but then got used to the walk and getting in touch with how Yangon residents live their daily lives ; although have to watch out walking in the dark as the pavements are serious hazards even during daytime.|As for the staff and their English or non-English, for Myanmar that has just opened up to the world, it is quite exciting to try and communite with someone who does not speak English. Otherwise we might as well not travel anymore.|My reservations about Wardan Hotel is breakfast that could be improved smartly. Also, the receptionists need to take the initiative to help the clients with their requirements especially when it comes to booking outside services so that the clients know exactly what to expect in services and costs.||Overall for the rates I paid I am very satisfied.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Krista E","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QdCjMUwIiBikRhCLHgN_0vyGAo1GvT8DEukiKQb1ujC_eFsFjYrQ0OvLoSxPtqmCdgvFA=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Nothing special about this place, but nothing bad either.  Room was fairly large, but bathroom fairly small and non-sensical as the shower drain was on the SIDE of the shower (gravity, folks).  The room is very sparse and felt a bit prison-like, and the bed was hard enough to make prisoners cry.  AC worked great, though, and internet surprisingly well.||||Friendly check-in and then didn't see a soul again until check-out, which I suppose is fine.  Breakfast was slightly below average, but again with friendly service.  Not a great area to be in for Yangon as you are in Chinatown.||||Perfectly average for the price, which was relatively low.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Yaël C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qc_hSEOVyYt90T8jEI1lbdGPaVqSrwdtGLOma43xF2tT-AGCQEDWJCQ3qq81gsm_HjiWg=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"This hotel is basic. It lacks a bit of charm. Our rooms (2nd floor) were spatious but the bathroom shower leaked quite significantly and it's poorly finished. The staff is very nice but it is very difficult to communicate (very poor english) except with the lady manager (owner?) who speaks better english and who was very helpful. Unfortunately she wasn't there when we arrived in Yangon (2 nights). We were very happy to have her on our last night in Yangon (coming back from Ngapali).||Breakfast is really.... local! fried rice (very good), soup, noodles, but no croissants or \"the usual stuff\"! The hotel itself was not noisy but the street is, especially early morning.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Aniell E","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QfjHmZg8gr7jpDgKhrh5KsR_Mq7L6pkVedvpKQz-f3LMiOd3OjI90CK4uLtF3wE59zZgA=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Average 3 star hotel, maybe a touch expensive compared to what you may get in Phnom Penh Cambodia, (check out Le Grande Palais). Breakfast was certainly sufficient, buffet style and marginally above average. No reason to complain but I am a man who is simply pleased!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"hounds","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QfsTQkcy2KndgDISqLavaj05iVMNn3XOI6udcho2AN-fABBAw5poEMIHSoJIZdEEshKkA=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Considering the other options in Yangon, the hotel is a good value. The beds are comfy, and the rooms are on a relatively quiet street.  In the early morning, the street vendors outside the hotel gather to sell meat, fish, and other items, and the smell upon stepping a bit from the hotel is overwhelming in the heat...but that's Yangon.  The free wifi was decent for Myanmar. I didn't think the location was a problem--it's a short walk to one of the main roads. title: Shannkalay Hostel
address: No.166/168, 3rd floor ,49th Street Between Bogyoke Aung San &, Anawrahta Rd, Yangon 11162
descriptions: Basic dorms & private rooms in an unfussy hostel offering breakfast & Wi-Fi, plus a balcony.
complete_address: {"borough":"","street":"No.166/168, 3rd floor ,49th Street Between Bogyoke Aung San \u0026, Anawrahta Rd","city":"Yangon","postal_code":"11162","state":"","country":"MM"}
user_reviews: [{"Name":"Maartje V","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qf66pF81jsVXBxevYxxL5FsdlDsKAngAUpJVE-hAwai1rl8J0QnYqktKV3UGdpbmNlc_A=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"This is a good hostel. The standard two persons rooms are clean. They are provided with a chair, a table, and a comfortable bed. They also provide you with a new toothbrush, toothpaste, shampoo and a hair comb. The airconditioning was also good. Unfortunately, the bathroom and toilets were not very clean. There was this person who had shaved himself and left his shaved hair at the sink - very nice of him. The next day, the hair was still there and the day after the next day I could still find hair. Nonetheless, this hostel really deserves its rewarded five stars. The personnel is really nice. They are very welcoming. In the morning you'll get a fresh breakfast with coffee or tea, toast, fried egg, toasts, jam, butter and water melon. A good way to start your day in Yangon!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Zoharon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWtbBNOllhOdQcCrfjpPgmgA0djkAF4NkjJGqfvqxlywEP8Lzm_IA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba8-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The room is very basic, But has great wifi, Aircon and hot water.\nOwner very helpful.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Louise S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QdVsxDWqDDLG62Q3M3dmLlHORJs5jz0NWRJO3cP21KtRNPfosO7RpofjnbUgpyNjOTDew=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"We stayed 3 nights at Shannkalay.  It's a little far from bus/ train station but still walkable.  We enjoyed our stay here. The owner is lovely ( and can sort tours, buses etc if you need them) and there are interesting photos and ornaments around the place. Comfortable bed and pillows. Good wifi in the room. Clean and nice touches with complimentary toothbrush, water etc.|Shared bathrooms are clean and good pressure in the showers ( hot water if you need it) |Most rooms don't have windows but you can ask for one if available  ( there's not a view but at least natural light.)|Nice breakfast on the balcony to watch the world go by. You can witness a monks alms collection happening below...Just listen for the gong .|Easy to walk to Sule pagoda and Bogyoke Aung san market  (Scott market)||We would recommend staying at Shannkalay hostel, especially if you like a more quiet place. |","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Bekah B","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QfHhPp0vyvo1Wo3WY4NH1G5QOPAHGBMv_XiebXLZtHzVwVa3wkRhb3dykyKrUCZPlawDA=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"A small but nice hostel in the middle of yangon. We had a private room, bed was comfy and they provided towels. No windows in the room but it was okay. Showers were good and hot, although sometimes the bathrooms smelled like drains. The hostel had no common area, but the staff were all very friendly.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Roxy Aung","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUzV84QupJM8u4ZsZum_u4Ioa1SR0U2IXHwrg_XhKsmSxnk0K8z=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The best you can get for the price in Yangon. Tiny rooms with air-conditioning, soft comfortable beds and clean bedding. Clean toilets and very good hot shower. Good breakfast in the morning on the balcony. The staff are very friendly and helpful. We have traveled with a baby and felt comfortable enough to get some rest for a few days. Feels like a home away from home. If you traveling on a budget with kids, this is the place to stay in Yangon.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Robert C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QfnSFWXMd1oJu73a6IhdtgibYcjse2HKQTHeghNQd9Cyw8DYQQJZDCyh-TD68ehXuY-FA=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Staff were always helpful and smiling. Bagan room has one huge double and one single bed, nicely decorated, quiet at the back of the hostel despite being near the toilet facilities. Breakfast is good. WiFi OK but sim worth purchasing at airport. Cheap and good eateries located very near by.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kirsimarja Helppi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJDp2I1jM3VKtdOzypbOIE3Gfd02bQ2dTpCE9s6CuPOHFfpVQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"If you want the feeling of a home away from home while in Myanmar, get a room at Shannkalay Hostel! You'd never believe it climbing up a damp, muggy, green-coloured staircase up to the third floor, but the ambiance once you take your shoes off and step in the door is ever so restful. The place is clean and the bedding (aside from the rather high pillows) is simply divine. You'll sleep like a baby! During our three week trip to Myanmar and Thailand, we stayed at four different hotels and one hostel. Some of the hotels were of the finest quality, but the Shannkalay beat every one of them by a long shot. The next time we visit Yangon, this is the place we'll choose as the place to stay for the whole time.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Rommel T","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QfnSFWXMd1oJu73a6IhdtgibYcjse2HKQTHeghNQd9Cyw8DYQQJZDCyh-TD68ehXuY-FA=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Apart from its proximity to many tourist attractions, the hostel is awesome. It's clean and affordable with free breakfast and good wifi connection. The receptionist is very friendly, kind, considerate and accommodating. A perfect place to stay to solo travellers with tight budget.","Images":null,"When":""}]

title: Hotel Kamarkyi
address: No7,Kamarkyi road,8th quarter, Yangon
descriptions: Warmly decorated rooms in an unpretentious hotel offering a restaurant & a fitness center.
user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Win Mar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUY81owTtmMzrjereg1c86bHiG8bHe_JbLoVzGe45YGUQOHyE8=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Breakfast is not bad and you can watch morning views on the rooftop. It's cool 😎. Service is not bad and the room is not bad. But water is strange. The location is very good and easy to get there.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Simon Hehe","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUj7zKdHHDw9y-DOnzqO3zzeZvCxWgVNgrGR0NJs-H1h7fJhgI=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Food-the variety was underwhelming to say the least and it was decent at best.Quite the disappointment I suppose.

Facilities-Just the gym, no spa, and no nothing. The gym is quite facilitied but the machines are broken(running machines) which is quite sad considering the fact that that was the selling point of the gym tbh. But there certainly is one for each type of exercise-lats, triceps, biceps, legs, and arms. But there is only about one for each which ain't that much but it gets the job done.

Rooms-we didn't get those typa "expensive and luxurious" rooms and got a family room and a superior double bed. The family room was quite capacious but the superior one was quite small, might be due to the price but it's to be expected.

Service-A lil over average ova. The speed is consistent and when we ordered some snacks from the hotel, both time, the order were sent within 20min and the taste was restruant type quality and the prices were quite inexpensive considering the tax and service fees that were added ova.

Conclusion-A great hotel, was great for the price. View was somewhat great with the river side view but am not a photo takin typa guy so what would I know:3 the services werent bad. Would recommend if you're in the area and just want to get the night over with. But if you want to get a feel of luxury and comfort, this place does offer some but there are many places that are better but this is one of the best 3-stars hotel imo{i don't rlly lodge in 3 stars but from what I've seen, this is by far the best one yet, tho ion understand why there ain't a spa or onsen:(}

Ova? Would recommend if u be in a hurry.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Nyein Su San","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK26icXTn8zKGGw63se8qYK3x72r3wWpnBhFLhQVT1zZ-O81Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"For the first day, they take extra charges 10000 MMK for children under 10.

But make sure to book in advance for daycation. Always full on weekends.

Rooms are really neat and tidy. Great for quick romantic getaways. ;)

Oh it has limited parking space on the second floor.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Su San","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL3eVTgVQzYli1nWhZKF4JU47nj7GrW4Rz0-YKvBgYx6jn5vbg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Quiet place to nap.
Late check out is not allowed even for 3pm though my check in was 9pm.
And our family stayed there 4 nights.
No favour was shown upon my request.
Breakfast was not up to standard like 2019.
I will look into another hotel next time.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Htike Aung Kyaw (ထိုက်အောင်ကျော်)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXPg11AiMc4bQilh5xSPvnX1bN9Xrh58DFsOWdiTAB6ECrWVZuLrQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Seems overrated. We checked-in around 3PM. Says you can check-in starting at 2PM. But when we arrived, the room wasn't quite ready yet. They were still fixing the water heater. They informed us that we'll be able to use hot water by night-time. The Side Table and Stools weren't even arranged properly when we arrived. We specifically requested the lake view room but was allocated at the 5th floor where the lake can't be seen as it's covered by trees. Still we get the view of Shwedagon Pagoda though. The room was hot, humid and a bit dusty when we checked in. Bed sheets are stained in some places but we didn't complain. What I was disgusted most by is the mold in Shower Curtains. Yuck! And hair remains in the bathtub and floor near the bed. At night, I turned on hot water and all I got was air, rusted brown water and cold water. I called them to check and they came in claiming the water is usable and is warm. It wasn't. Don't let me start with the room key card... Works 1 out of 30 tries. They came to change batteries both in the evening and the next morning. Every time we get out of the room we get locked out even though we have the key card with us. The only good thing was the tasty breakfast with a wide variety to choose from. Even for breakfast, the dining room arrangement sucked. They put two extra tables and chairs close to the buffet table and we have to tuck through these to get the food. Ugh... And they rang the doorbell at 7 AM mistakenly with the next room who were to check-out that morning. Didn't even say they were sorry for the interruption. We were given breakfast tickets but when we arrived at the dining room, no one was there to collect it so we left these tickets on the table after we were done eating. Guess what? They called us at 9AM and said it was the last call for breakfast. Good that they remind us for Breakfast, bad that they suck at who has finished eating and who have not. Overall, it seems overrated and overpriced compared to other hotels in town. Maybe they treat us locals differently from foreigners, not sure about that, as the room rates for locals and foreigners are different. But I think, for the same price, there are many hotels out there that give better service and facilities than those provided here.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOTjv-D6zKesrZz3a9TCruPYLhsrV5_JvBM9upK&fid=0x0:0xf4763ad7a8ba89c5"],"When":"2023-6-3"}]

title: Royal Boss Hotel
address: No. 232 - A, Yamonnar Street, Waso Quarter, Dawbon Township, Yangon 11221
complete_address: {"borough":"","street":"No. 232 - A, Yamonnar Street, Waso Quarter, Dawbon Township","city":"Yangon","postal_code":"11221","state":"","country":"MM"}
user_reviews: [{"Name":"Steve W","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeFH6dzZjd_ZFLhXHZKibEzXEy8hWzFB4Qa7PutLe3CnO2G7yVfjd4VSabiCQwQYo5W-g=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"I really like this hotel.  The owners are Burmese but have lived in the States, so they understand independent travelers, and can communicate in English very well. They were super friendly and very nice.  When we were sick and wanted some Chinese porridge they went out of their way and made us some complimentary bowls even though it wasn't on their menu. the hotel is only 4 months old and in a good location as a spring board to downtown and shwedagon.  Wifi fast enough for my VPN so i could hook up to my work.  outside are some tasty eating stalls and local restaurants. Although breakfast is included try the breakfast soup behind the wood fence on the left as you exit the hotel, or grab some crepes (morning) or roti (night) there as well.  chinese you tao and burmese sweet tea are on the right as you exit.  Everything about a 30 second walk.  Great stay.  I booked only 1 night but ended up staying for 4.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"yingyan w","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QcAMX6x1kyyC4a8uKPBZCeWlT90KjmNFkgsk2nwAxhNYMl35txt0LKhr7WJeqrhDy9dMA=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"It is not exactly a budget hotel, but I can't classify it as a hostel either. A very small scale 4 storey hotel, which is very new. Rooms come with balcony that allows you to catch a glimpse of the quieter side of the town, and you can see the famous shwedagon from far far away too.. ||we stayed for 1 night before leaving myanmar, the room was clean, and toilet was big by yangon standards. the furniture, tv channels, bathroom fittings, were all china originated, so for some moments, it did feel like we're in china. everything works fine, and most importantly they're new!! ||the owners used to live in US, since they're the third generation of burmese chinese, they speak fluent chinese and english. the boss was very kind, and offered to buy me cough medications when he realised i was sick. the lady boss also provided a lot of suggestions on what to do in town too. ||the room had mosquitoes, like all other places we stayed in myanmar, but the counter staff kindly offered her bottle of room-use insecticide. ||breakfast was the standard bread, fruits (the boss buys the fruits daily from the chinatown market), tea, 2 eggs. we paid $35 a night, which was the most expensive room we had in the entire myanmar trip. but it's worth the price, i feel, as another place wanted to charge us $37 a night, for non-ac, no window room. ||will definitely consider coming back again next time, if location isn't a concern for the next trip.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Paul J","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qd0Gzx7-o-W0qn7F-oHhorx-ann6UFYRniBmE7Ar1MhRFtO-x6vY7U2LNCPC1lcQidkpw=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Well run modern, clean, nice quiet location only a $2 cab from Cbd. $35 per night inc an average breakfast. Better than $100 rooms in the Cbd. Staff's grasp of English is not great. Owned by charming elderly Chinese couple. Has WiFi. Taxi stand out front. Public buses on road out front, which run into town regularly. Meals are just OK. Fried Rice is fine. Stumbled across this place whilst randomly searching for hotels by Taxi after bad experiences and pricing in the CBD area. Stayed 5 nights. Good neighbourhood to explore. Enjoy","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Roseanne C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QfnSFWXMd1oJu73a6IhdtgibYcjse2HKQTHeghNQd9Cyw8DYQQJZDCyh-TD68ehXuY-FA=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"I came to `Burma for a 3 week trip starting in January and stayed at the Fatherland for my first 3 nights and last night. It was clean, with delightful staff and owners who live on the top floor. It was a 20 minute taxi ride into town which cost £1.50. The staff helped me catch local buses, book buses and accommodation and taught me Burmese phrases. I stayed here again when I returned to Yangon before my flight home. This is a good option for an affordable room in Yangoon. My room had a balcony so I could watch the world go by. I was a solo female traveller in a new country so I really appreciated the kindness the staff at this hotel showed me.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Maria S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qf66pF81jsVXBxevYxxL5FsdlDsKAngAUpJVE-hAwai1rl8J0QnYqktKV3UGdpbmNlc_A=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"The hotel was opened on 2012 by the owner and the rooms are clean and modern. $35/per night (breakfast includes) for the regular standard room with Wifi which is cheaper than other hotels that are charging $80 per night with the same service. It's easy to take taxi to anywhere and the service is wonderful. title: YAMA HOTEL & ROOFTOP BAR
address: Block 9, YAMA HOTEL & ROOFTOP BAR, No. 195, Street Bo Myat Htun St, 11111
descriptions: Plain dorms & streamlined private rooms in a contemporary hotel with a rooftop bar & free Wi-Fi.
user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Thet Htar Hsu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKLcnPPg6PPnkivAcNBjMBxHU4UFUNZy-lMMf86jJH_Gbw59uA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Absolutely Terrible Experience – Do Not Stay Here

This hotel charged us for “damaging” their TV, claiming we somehow updated the system and caused it to stop working. Here’s what really happened: we were simply watching YouTube on the TV when it suddenly turned off. How is that our fault? The manager pulled out their terms and conditions, which apparently state “do not update the TV system”. Excuse me, but why would anyone randomly update a TV system in the middle of the night? That’s absurd.

If their system is so sensitive that a regular guest could accidentally cause “damage,” why even offer it as a service? Why wasn’t there a clear warning at check-in? This is beyond ridiculous.

At first, they blamed us for water damage to the remote. Then, suddenly, it wasn’t the remote—it was the TV itself! How convenient for them. The lack of professionalism and low-level management here is shocking. If this is how they handle guest issues, they shouldn’t be running a hotel.

I wouldn’t recommend this place to anyone. Save yourself the frustration and stay somewhere else. This so-called “hotel” is a complete joke.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Philip Neri","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWrfJUJvkoZwcJJv1tDh2vcvrCmNmTqe18iTPFfCHLfrzeOPWby=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Nice hotel with fair price in this location.
